) VALUES (
  '82f6649d-f8d6-4da3-9704-d69b2f37d1a1',
  'Session Commander Architecture Guide — Unified Session Coordination System',
  'session-commander-architecture-guide',
  'Architecture guide explaining how the 5 components of the Session Commander system (Coordinator, SessionMonitor, RetryStrategy, Feedback, Types) integrate into a unified session resilience architecture.',
  'architecture',
  'architecture_doc',
  'typescript',
  ARRAY['session-commander','architecture-guide','session-management','refresh-coordination','resilience','deduplication','exponential-backoff','visibility-api','event-driven'],
  E'/**\n * Session Commander Architecture Guide\n *\n * SYSTEM OVERVIEW:\n * The Session Commander is the SINGLE POINT OF CONTROL for all session-related\n * operations in a SaaS application. It replaces fragmented refresh logic\n * with a centralized, event-driven coordination system.\n *\n * COMPONENT MAP (5 files):\n *\n * SessionCommander (index.ts) — Singleton facade\n *   ├── RefreshCoordinator (coordinator.ts) — Deduplication + retry + backend call\n *   ├── SessionMonitor (session-monitor.ts) — visibilitychange + online + focus + adaptive intervals\n *   ├── RetryStrategy (retry-strategy.ts) — Exponential backoff + jitter + sleep + tabId\n *   ├── Feedback (feedback.ts) — Reconnecting/reconnected/expired toasts via Sonner\n *   └── Types (types.ts) — RefreshResult, CommanderState, SessionHealth, Config\n *\n * DATA FLOW:\n * 1. SessionMonitor detects event (tab visible, online, focus)\n * 2. SessionMonitor calls onCheck callback\n * 3. onCheck triggers SessionCommander.requestRefresh()\n * 4. SessionCommander delegates to RefreshCoordinator\n * 5. RefreshCoordinator deduplicates (returns existing Promise if active)\n * 6. RefreshCoordinator calls backend with AbortController timeout\n * 7. Backend returns: success | wait | unauthorized | error\n * 8. On wait: sleep(retryAfter), retry without incrementing attempt\n * 9. On error: getExponentialDelay(), retry\n * 10. On success/final failure: Feedback shows appropriate toast\n *\n * DEDUPLICATION: Multiple callers → same Promise via refreshQueue field\n * SERVER COORDINATION: Backend returns wait+retryAfter when another tab holds lock\n */\n\nimport { sessionCommander } from ''@/lib/session-commander'';\n\n// Start monitoring (typically in AuthProvider useEffect)\nsessionCommander.startMonitoring(() => {\n  const tokenContext = getTokenContext();\n  if (needsRefresh(tokenContext)) {\n    sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\n  }\n});\n\n// Request refresh from anywhere (deduplicated)\nconst result = await sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\nif (!result.success && result.reason === ''expired'') {\n  redirectToLogin();\n}\n\n// Cleanup\nsessionCommander.stopMonitoring();',
  'Session management is the most fragile part of any SaaS application. Without centralized coordination, you get race conditions (multiple tabs refreshing simultaneously), thundering herd problems, and poor UX (no feedback during reconnection). The Session Commander architecture eliminates ALL of these with a composable system handling deduplication, server-side locking, exponential backoff with jitter, and visual feedback — all in ~500 lines across 5 focused files.',
  'Use when building any SaaS with JWT/cookie-based auth needing multi-tab support, network interruption handling, background tab throttling, and session expiration. Implement all 5 components together. Pairs with token-manager-architecture-guide.',
  E'// In your AuthProvider:\nimport { sessionCommander } from ''@/lib/session-commander'';\nimport { needsRefresh, getTokenContext } from ''@/lib/token-manager'';\n\nuseEffect(() => {\n  sessionCommander.startMonitoring(() => {\n    const ctx = getTokenContext();\n    if (needsRefresh(ctx)) {\n      sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\n    }\n  });\n  return () => sessionCommander.stopMonitoring();\n}, []);\n\n// In your API client interceptor:\nif (response.status === 401) {\n  const result = await sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\n  if (result.success) return retryRequest();\n  throw new SessionExpiredError();\n}',
  'risecheckout',
  'validated',
  'global',
  'advanced',
  120,
  'session-commander',
  0,
  ARRAY['aab502c7-22a2-4d44-8b96-2d01cf5e8a67','4c02c917-bc31-4040-9350-963ea9d73f45','19f2c74a-4612-471c-b26d-4ec2bd329628']::uuid[],
  ARRAY['multiple tabs refreshing simultaneously','thundering herd on network recovery','no feedback during session reconnection','background tab throttling breaks heartbeat','race condition between refresh and API calls','how to coordinate session refresh across components'],
  '[{"error":"TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading requestRefresh)","cause":"SessionCommander singleton not initialized","fix":"Import from @/lib/session-commander barrel export"},{"error":"Multiple toasts for same reconnection","cause":"Feedback called without isShowingFeedback check","fix":"Let RefreshCoordinator manage feedback state internally"},{"error":"Infinite refresh loop on 401","cause":"API interceptor retries but gets another 401","fix":"Mark request as already-retried with header flag"}]'::jsonb,
  E'const p1 = sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\nconst p2 = sessionCommander.requestRefresh();\nassert(p1 === p2, ''Same promise for concurrent calls'');\nsessionCommander.startMonitoring(() => {});\nassert(sessionCommander.isRefreshing() === false);\nsessionCommander.stopMonitoring();',
  E'## Overview\n\nThe Session Commander is a centralized session coordination system for SaaS applications with cookie-based authentication. It replaces the anti-pattern of scattering refresh logic across API interceptors, timers, and auth providers.\n\n## How it Works\n\n5 files, each with single responsibility:\n1. **SessionCommander** (index.ts) — Singleton facade. requestRefresh(), startMonitoring(), stopMonitoring().\n2. **RefreshCoordinator** (coordinator.ts) — Deduplication engine. Stores active Promise in refreshQueue. Handles retry with exponential backoff.\n3. **SessionMonitor** (session-monitor.ts) — Event-driven monitor. visibilitychange, online, focus events. Adaptive intervals (1min foreground, 5min background).\n4. **RetryStrategy** (retry-strategy.ts) — Pure functions for exponential backoff with ±25% jitter.\n5. **Feedback** (feedback.ts) — Visual notifications via Sonner toasts.\n\n## When to Use\n- Any SaaS with JWT or cookie-based auth\n- Multi-tab applications\n- Applications needing graceful network interruption handling\n\n## When NOT to Use\n- Static sites without authentication\n- Server-rendered applications (SSR)\n- Applications with very short-lived tokens (<5 min)\n\n## Security Considerations\n- No secrets sent to backend — only cookies via credentials: include\n- Cloudflare Worker gateway injects API key server-side\n- AbortController enforces 15s request timeout',
  '{"npm_dependencies":["sonner"],"env_vars_required":[],"ai_rules":["Always implement all 5 components together","Do NOT call feedback functions directly — let RefreshCoordinator manage visual state","SessionCommander is a singleton — never instantiate multiple instances"]}'::jsonb
);

